questions.question: Given data X = 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10 and 11 and respective values of Y for all X values are -2.369, 2.236, 9.094, 15.767, 21.120, 25.885 and 30.851. Find the value of Integration of Y with Simpson's (1/3) Rule.

Given data X = 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12 and 13 respective values of Y for all X values are 9.094, 15.767, 21.120, 25.885, 30.851, 34.078, 29.457. Find the value of Integration of Y with Simpson's (1/3) Rule.
